Ahem, returning to the demo review, there follows a decent variation of 
the warp-tunnel effect, as this one seems to get more pixels in it than 
normal, a higher than normal res version of a common effect..

Another chrome doughnut,  this time in a blue study follows,  a picture 
and some greetings/credits text,  and that is it.. Unlike another intro 
by Therapy, this one finishes properly in time with the music..

Ratings..

Graphics:-  88%  -  ICE have usually come up  with  some  nice  looking 
screens  in the past,  and this has been carried over to the Falcon  as 
well..

Sonix:-  80%  - Nothing special,  but jaunty little tune that fits  the 
demo perfectly..

Gee-Whiz:- 79% - Shiny happy people, er, doughnuts!

Overall:-  82% - Good debut for the Falcon,  when are you going to do a 
big demo for the Falcon?

